# Template Runtime Rules

Nextflow renders templates through Groovy before R, Python, or shell sees them.

- Escape bare `$` as `\$` unless it is an intentional `${...}` Nextflow substitution.
- Prefer R `[[]]` access over `$` in templates.
- Avoid raw `\n`, `\t`, and `\r` in Python template strings when Groovy rendering is involved; use `chr(10)` and `chr(9)` where safer.
- Set `NUMBA_CACHE_DIR=/tmp` before imports that can load numba/scanpy/umap inside Apptainer.
- Keep export, harmonize, and merge outputs sparse/raw unless the downstream model stage owns normalization.
- Inspect generated `.command.sh` when syntax errors or missing Groovy variables appear.
